VELOCHEETAH stalked three wide and between horses, brushed an inner foe at the half mile pole then weakened among foes turning for home. FRACING ALLSTAR broke a step slow and trailed throughout.

ROSARIO'S PRAYER lacked speed in the two to four paths and moved up. EFFICACIOUS broke outwardly, stalked three wide into the turn, pressed the leader from the three path entering the backstretch but wilted between horses around the far turn. FLORIS prompted along the inside while in the two path into the first turn, backed off to stalk around that bend, but weakened between horses approaching the far turn. CATHERINE BLAZE laid off of the pace in the two to three path, lacked a response to urging in the four path with nine sixteenths to go and was done early. THE RIDER OF MIDNINGHTCANDYSTORM CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE RIDER OF EAST SHORE FOR INTERFERENCE IN MIDSTRETCH; FOLLOWING THE OBJECTION, AS WELL AS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY REVIEWING THE SAME INFRACTION, NO CHANGE WAS MADE TO THE ORIGINAL ORDER OF FINISH.
